# Backend: Event-Driven Architecture

## Core Principle
Every side-effect (email, notification, audit log, cache invalidation) **must be triggered through an event**, never called directly from the business logic layer.

## Module Structure

```
src/
  modules/
    <domain>/
      commands/         # CQRS Commands + Handlers
      queries/          # CQRS Queries + Handlers
      events/           # Domain events (plain TS classes)
      listeners/        # EventEmitter2 / CQRS event handlers
      dto/              # Data Transfer Objects
      <domain>.module.ts
      <domain>.service.ts
      <domain>.controller.ts
      <domain>.repository.ts
  common/
    events/             # Shared event base classes
    filters/            # Exception filters
    guards/             # Auth guards
    interceptors/       # Logging, transform interceptors
    decorators/         # Custom decorators
  prisma/               # PrismaService singleton
  workers/              # Bull queue processors (CPU-bound / async work)
```

## Event Naming Convention

```typescript
// ✅ Domain event class — past tense, PascalCase
export class UserCreatedEvent {
  constructor(
    public readonly userId: string,
    public readonly email: string,
    public readonly occurredAt: Date = new Date(),
  ) {}
}
```

## Emitting Events

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — emit after persisting
import { EventEmitter2 } from '@nestjs/event-emitter';

@Injectable()
export class UserService {
  constructor(
    private readonly userRepo: UserRepository,
    private readonly events: EventEmitter2,
  ) {}

  async createUser(dto: CreateUserDto) {
    const user = await this.userRepo.create(dto);
    this.events.emit('user.created', new UserCreatedEvent(user.id, user.email));
    return user;
  }
}
```

## Listening to Events

```typescript
// ✅ Listener — decoupled side-effect
@Injectable()
export class UserNotificationListener {
  @OnEvent('user.created', { async: true })
  async handleUserCreated(event: UserCreatedEvent) {
    // send welcome email — fully decoupled from UserService
  }
}
```

## Async / CPU-bound Work → Bull Queue

Any task > 50 ms or likely to fail/retry must go through a Bull queue processor in `src/workers/`:

```typescript
@Processor('email')
export class EmailProcessor {
  @Process('send-welcome')
  async sendWelcome(job: Job<{ userId: string }>) { ... }
}
```

## CQRS for Complex Domains

Use `@nestjs/cqrs` for domains with complex read/write separation:
- Commands mutate state — one handler per command, never query inside a command handler.
- Queries read state — never emit events or mutate inside a query handler.
